project.title: Mortal Engines - London Weapons
project.description:
Concept art for the film Mortal Engines (2018) 
I ended up doing a heckuva lot of drawings for this film over a ten year period at Weta Workshop. This first batch is some of the designs for weapons that were to be seen in the city of London. There's a bunch more vehicles, characters and weapons that I'll post up on here soon.
Lotsa fun! Was cool seeing some of these get built by super skilled craftspeople!

project.description:
Here is Feng my ongoing project, I hope to post soon the rest of it !
She is actually a rework of an old character I created with a teammate 2 years ago, therefore the process was different from usual. 
Feng is the right arm of a powerful asian mafia in a near futur and hides her identity/occupation; I had fun making those 2 outfits accordingly and go out of my comfort zone with some streetwear or regular non fantasy fashion ! I really want to show other aspects of this character  as well as the process sketches very soon !

project.title: Khedemar- Prophet's Respite
project.description: The stepwells of Prophets Respite; an ethereal plane that the Prophets of Khedemar head to when gathering power and formulating thoughts. This is a meditation chamber of sorts where the thoughts of all beings are shared, where one mind merges with another, and all ideas become one. This concept is reflected in the seemingly neverending stepwells of this world, with infinite areas to descend into. The last frames show the threads of life, inactive and active, as they start to bind materials together.

project.title: Overwatch - Kanezaka
project.description:
Kanezaka is a deathmatch map set in the shadows of the Hanamura castle.


I worked mostly on the modern area of the map, taking it from blockout to art final, including some lighting and most of the textures. The buildings in this area were mostly inspired by my trip to Tokyo a few years back. I tried to capture the vibe of the place as best as I could, so the user can be transported to Japan while playing. I'm a huge fan of this kind of architecture, and had a blast working on it! It was also the first map that I used Substance Designer extensively (though I still touched up my textures by hand on Photoshop). This' also the first map we made fully working from home :)


Credits:
Level design:  Morten Hedegren
Traditional area architecture: Helder Pinto
Hanamura castle: Philip Klevestav
Lighting: Fabien Christin
Concepts: Peter Lee, Llia Yu, Andrew Menjivar
Polish, foliage: Dion Rogers
Props: Lindsay Johnson, Courtney Vogel
Producer: Kim Horn


Little piece of trivia: My two cats (along with other cats from team members) are featured in the cat caf√© :D

project.title: Rural Cabins
project.description:
Until this point I never made a modular wall set. I wanted to learn how to do this because I think it is an essential skill to have as an environment artist. When I was making the set I realized wanted to create a full environment around it.
My goal was to capture a small town in the American mid-west.
This is how it turned out!
If you want to play around with it yourself you can get it here: https://www.unrealengine.com/marketplace/en-US/product/2ddbe37c08db4ca3abf0b178aae465bf
